[5] United States (Massachusetts)
Date: Fri 27 Jul 2018
Source: India New England [edited]
http://indianewengland.com/2018/07/boston-officials-alert-of-potential-measles-exposure-in-the-city/


The Boston Public Health Commission (BPHC) on Fri [27 Jul 2018] alerted the public of a potential measles exposure at 2 Boston locations, after receiving notification of a confirmed case of measles.

Anyone who visited the following locations during the specified dates and times could become ill between 26 Jul and 10 Aug 2018: [see URL for locations, including Logan airport, and times].

BPHC recommends monitoring for symptoms and contacting their health care provider.

BPHC is working with other health officials on this case and monitoring for potential exposures. BPHC has also reached out to Boston residents to increase awareness about risk of exposure and encourage people who were potentially exposed to call their health care provider by phone for further instructions.

For additional information, see: http://www.bphc.org/whatwedo/infectious-diseases/Infectious-Diseases-A-to-Z/Pages/Measles.aspx.

